will my year old remember me i'm deployed right now and i havent seen my son in months does anyone know if he will still remember me when i get home my husband deploys very frequently for a year at a time we have little girls ages and i show the girls pictures they talk to him on the phone and we have used a webcam in the past i also talk to them about daddy a lot as far as how your son will act upon your return each child is different my oldest was very apprehensive when she saw her dad after months she'd just stare at him but whimper when he'd try to engage her in play then she'd reach her finger out to touch him maybe to see if he was real but if he touched her back she'd cry finally we just let her touch her dad as much as she wanted without his reciprocating it was then that she opened up and it was as if they'd never been apart my middle daughter acted as though there had been no time apart at all when she saw her dad after months there was no shyness apprehension or anything i'm interested to see how my baby is going to react when she sees her dad at christmas it will have been a month separation for her don't worry even if it takes a little while you and your son will be close again when you get home About a Boy Little Girl Lost (The Twilight Zone) Father's Day (Doctor Who) Shaggy dog story Social rule Child sexuality Full House Friends The Shining (film) Bro'Town Salad Fingers Dad's Army Miss Saigon Jon Secada Grandview, U.S.A. The Fairly OddParents Infantilism The Adventures of Pete & Pete Milton H. Erickson Sharon Tate Family Guy Kodocha Code: Lyoko Avenue Q Pitaten Episodes of Lost (Season 1) EastEnders The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Neighbours What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film) The Beatles discography Grey Dawn Hey Jude Fathers' rights The Life and Times of Juniper Lee The Inside Knots Landing Sin City Prank flash Doug House of M Who Shot Mr. Burns? The Flintstones Garfield The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Rais massacre Cliff Richard Hall & Oa